collection.description: Recordings from conversations in partnership with Reimagine Arkansas
collection.title: Reimagine Arkansas

highlights.description: klein book points out that govts have used national crises (e.g. 9/11, iraq war) to implement friedman-esque economic policy that worsens underlying structural issues and injustices
speaks to the importance of having schools open, because lots of kids rely heavily on school for food, healthy relationships, etc on top of education

I actually had no idea what a quorum court was — sounds like they are the legislative branch of county governments in AR, and they allocate spending on basic services like infrastructure, police, etc. — for folks who live in a place that isn't incorporated into a city, this is an especially big deal
Challenge the systems instead of the symptoms
